-- Citi, Goldman among banks to meet Obama on Monday
-- 
-- Thu Dec 10, 2009 9:47am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/12/10/us-obama-banks-idUSTRE5B92U520091210

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Twelve major banks, including Citigroup Inc, Goldman Sachs Group Inc and JPMorgan Chase & Co, will participate in a White House meeting with President Barack Obama on Monday, an administration official said on Thursday. 

 Obama has summoned the bankers to press them to increase lending to small businesses and discuss his administration's financial regulatory reform efforts. Other executives attending the previously announced meeting come from: * Bank of America Corp * Wells Fargo & Co * Capital One Financial Corp * American Express Co. * Bank of New York Mellon Corp * Morgan Stanley * PNC Financial Services Group Inc * U.S. Bancorp * State Street Corp (Reporting by  Matt Spetalnick )